In contrast, in the town where we now live, teachers have access to the mobile bagel app and are sharing what they have learned in their geography classes with their students. And if we don't have people who live and work in a particular place, how can we expect that they will learn anything about the environment where they live?

The setup of mobile bagel is not only great for geography teachers. It will also benefit the students because they will be able to interact with experts in non-scientific areas who are not teachers and have applied knowledge in their fields.

Mobile bagel can inform nature and research and allocate among students and city experts.

I have friends in my village who have a passion for science and technology.

In the future, it will be easier for them to communicate and share their knowledge independently, without having to move around.

We all want to have a better life and to have a life, we need to have money in our pockets.

As such, I believe that knowledge can only be gained through education.
